Version 1.3 (25.12.2015):
- Decoding: Now driven by interrupts to make timing accuracy unaffected by high CPU load
- Decoding: Ring buffer for each sample containing state, length and RSSI
- Decoding: Supports RAW mode with RSSI treshold
- Decoding: Supports NEXA self-learning dimming packet (used by door and PIR sensor)
- Decoding: Supports NEXA code wheel packet
- Lines terminated with CRLF rather than LF
- Automatically loads default settings on configuration version mismatch (after upgrading)
- Default baud rate changed to 115200
- Removed BMC mode (custom protocol)
